# NSImage.LoadStatus.invalidData

**Case**

An error occurred during image decompression.

## Declaration

```swift
case invalidData
```

## Discussion

The image data is probably corrupt. The image contains the portions of the data that have already been successfully decompressed, if any.

## Load Status Values

- **NSImage.LoadStatus.completed**: Enough data is available to completely decompress the image.
- **NSImage.LoadStatus.cancelled**: Image loading was canceled.
- **NSImage.LoadStatus.unexpectedEOF**: Not enough data was available to fully decompress the image.
- **NSImage.LoadStatus.readError**: Not enough data was available for full decompression of the image.
